Command Description <code>)wsid</code> Show the current workspace ID <code>)wsid name</code> Set the workspace ID to <code>name</code> <code>)save</code> Save the workspace to <code>workspaces/{wsid}/</code>. Requires WSID to be set. <code>)save name</code> Set WSID to <code>name</code> and save <code>)load name</code> Load workspace <code>name</code> from <code>workspaces/</code> <code>)clear</code> Clear the workspace and reset WSID to <code>CLEAR WS</code> <code>)lib</code> List available workspaces <p>A fresh session starts with workspace ID <code>CLEAR WS</code>. You must set a WSID before saving:</p> <pre><code>      )wsid
CLEAR WS
      )save
ERROR: No workspace ID set. Use )WSID name first.
      )wsid mywork
mywork
      )save
mywork SAVED
</code></pre>
